from matplotlib import cm
from scipy import signal
import math as m
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d.axes3d import get_test_data

x=np.linspace(-10,10, num=100)
y=np.linspace(-10,10, num=100)

sigma = 1
X_ = np.arange(-5, 5.1, .1)
Y_ = np.arange(-5, 5.1, .1)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(X_,Y_)
Z = np.exp(-(X**2 + Y**2)/(2*m.pi*sigma**2))

# X Partial Derivative
sobel_ver_kernal = np.array([(-1, -2, -1), (0, 0, 0), (1, 2, 1)], dtype='float32')
#X_Der = signal.convolve2d(Z, sobel_ver_kernal, boundary='symm', mode='same') # scipy convolution 2D
X_Der = cv.filter2D(Z, -1, sobel_ver_kernal)

# Y Partial Derivative
sobel_hor_kernal = np.array([(-1, 0, 1), (-2, 0, 2), (-1, 0, 1)], dtype='float32')
#Y_Der = signal.convolve2d(Z, sobel_hor_kernal, boundary='symm', mode='same') # scipy convolution 2D
Y_Der = cv.filter2D(Z, -1, sobel_hor_kernal)

Gradient = np.sqrt(X_Der**2 + Y_Der**2)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(30,30))
ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 1, projection='3d')
surf = ax.plot_surface(X, Y, X_Der,  cmap=cm.jet, linewidth=0, antialiased=True)
ax.set_title("X Partial Derivative of Gaussian Filter Surface Plot")
ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 2, projection='3d')
surf = ax.plot_surface(X, Y, Y_Der,  cmap=cm.jet, linewidth=0, antialiased=True)
ax.set_title("Y Partial Derivative of Gaussian Filter Surface Plot")
ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 3, projection='3d')
surf = ax.plot_surface(X, Y, Gradient,  cmap=cm.jet, linewidth=0, antialiased=True)
ax.set_title("Gradient of Gaussian Filter Surface Plot")
plt.show()

gray = np.float32(gray)
dst = cv.cornerHarris(gray,2,3,0.04)
dst = cv.dilate(dst,None)
Output_Img2[dst>0.01*dst.max()]=[0, 0, 255]

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(20,20))

import skimage
from skimage.feature import peak_local_max

Img3 = cv.imread(r'building.tif', cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
Output_Img3 = cv.imread(r'building.tif', cv.IMREAD_COLOR)

I = cv.cvtColor(Output_Img3, cv.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
I = np.float32(I)
sobel_ver_kernal = np.array([(-1, -2, -1), (0, 0, 0), (1, 2, 1)], dtype='float32')
sobel_hor_kernal = np.array([(-1, 0, 1), (-2, 0, 2), (-1, 0, 1)], dtype='float32')

Ix = cv.filter2D(I, -1, sobel_ver_kernal)
Iy = cv.filter2D(I, -1, sobel_hor_kernal)

sigma = 3
ksize = 7
m11 = cv.GaussianBlur(Ix*Ix, (ksize, ksize), sigma)
m12 = cv.GaussianBlur(Ix*Iy, (ksize, ksize), sigma)
m21 = m12
m22 = cv.GaussianBlur(Iy*Iy, (ksize, ksize), sigma)

det = m11*m22-m12*m21
trace = m11 + m22
alpha = 0.04
R = det - alpha*trace**2
R[ R < 1e8] = 0
coordinates = peak_local_max(R, min_distance=2)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15,15))
ax[0,0].imshow(Img3, cmap = 'gray')
ax[0,0].set_title('Haris Corner Image'), ax[0,0].set_xticks([]), ax[0,0].set_yticks([])
ax[0,0].plot(coordinates[:,1], coordinates[:, 0], 'r.')
ax[0,1].imshow(Ix + 127, cmap = 'gray')
ax[0,1].set_title('Ix Image'), ax[0,1].set_xticks([]), ax[0,1].set_yticks([])
ax[1,0].imshow(Iy + 127, cmap = 'gray')
ax[1,0].set_title('Iy Image'), ax[1,0].set_xticks([]), ax[1,0].set_yticks([])
ax[1,1].imshow(R + 127, cmap=cm.jet)
ax[1,1].set_title('R Image'), ax[1,1].set_xticks([]), ax[1,1].set_yticks([])
plt.show()
